cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with natural language semantics. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also a likely category, as the paper discusses the use of lambda calculus in modeling natural language denotations. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category, as the paper discusses side effects in programming languages. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category, as the paper deals with natural language semantics, which is a key area of research in AI. 

cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper discusses the interaction between natural language semantics and programming language semantics, which could be relevant to software engineering.
